description: The final piece of the moments set, the story behind which is 100% true. I have a cello recital on the fourth with my cello choir, and as much as I need to practice my part in "Macabre for Four Cellos", I would rather not die of heat stroke alone in my room, and thus the air conditioning made it nearly impossible for me to play the right notes. What I was able to play sounded just about as non-complex and simple as this, although altogether I think it sounds pretty interesting.
title: Moment V. Practicing for a Cello Recital With the A.C. BLARING
